itemDescription: British Antarctic scientist who won the 1975 Fuchs Medal of the British Antarctic Survey (BAS) in recognition of her service to the BAS and its predecessor the Falklands Islands Dependencies Survey (FIDS)

wikipedia_page.main: Eleanor Honnywill (1919 or 1920 – 11 April 2003, born Eleanor Biscoe, later Lady Eleanor Fuchs) was instrumental in supporting the work of British Antarctic Survey (BAS).
